'''Ethyl pentanoate''', also commonly known as ethyl valerate, is an [[organic compound]] used in flavors.  It is an [[ester]] with the molecular formula C<sub>7</sub>H<sub>14</sub>O<sub>2</sub>.  This colorless liquid is poorly soluble in water but [[miscible]] with organic solvents.

As is the case with most volatile esters, it has a pleasant aroma and taste.  It is used as a [[food additive]] to impart a fruity flavor, particularly of apple.

