'''Focal socialisation agency''' ([[American and British English spelling differences#-ise.2C_-ize_.28-isation.2C_-ization.29|or]] '''focal socialization agency''') in [[sociology]] is the name given to the [[Agency (sociology)|agency]] which is most influential in process of [[socialisation]] upon an individual. Typically the first focal socialisation agency is the [[Sociology of the family|family]] but is usually succeeded in this role by the [[sociology of education|education system]] upon the entering of education.

