== Other related parties ==
The Dutch [[Party for Freedom]] (PVV), the Polish [[Congress of the New Right]] (KNP) and the German [[Alternative for Germany]] (AfD), despite not being members of MENL, participate in its political group in the European Parliament, [[Europe of Nations and Freedom|ENL]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/meps/en/search.html?politicalGroup=4907 |title=European Parliament : MEPs |website=Europarl.europa.eu |accessdate=2016-04-03}}</ref>

MENL leaders also have public political relations of some kind with [[Brothers of Italy]] (FdI, Italy)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europaquotidiano.it/2014/04/02/destra-marine-le-pen-incontra-giorgia-meloni-e-gianni-alemanno/ |title=Destra, Marine Le Pen incontra Giorgia Meloni e Gianni Alemanno (video) &#124; Europa Quotidiano |website=Europaquotidiano.it |date=2003-07-28 |accessdate=2016-04-03}}</ref> and [[Freedom and Direct Democracy]] (SPD, Czech Republic).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parlamentnilisty.cz/arena/monitor/Tomio-Okamura-svolal-vsechny-sve-lidi-a-bylo-rusno-Nepratelsti-vetrelci-Pokus-o-vrazdu-Delegace-od-Marine-Le-Pen-i-provolani-k-Zemanovi-412586 |title=Tomio Okamura svolal všechny své lidi a bylo rušno: Nepřátelští vetřelci! Pokus o vraždu. Delegace od Marine Le Pen i provolání k Zemanovi &#124; ParlamentniListy.cz – politika ze všech stran |website=Parlamentnilisty.cz |date= |accessdate=2016-04-03}}</ref> The latter is now a full member of the pan-European party.

In February 2016, FPÖ's leader [[Heinz-Christian Strache]] was invited by the anti-Euro & [[Opposition to immigration|anti-immigration]] party [[Alternative for Germany|AfD]] and its leader [[Frauke Petry]] to their congress in [[Düsseldorf]] and the AfD also announced a cooperation pact with the FPÖ.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://derstandard.at/2000031396307/Deutsche-AfD-und-FPOe-beschliessen-Zusammenarbeit |title=Deutsche AfD und FPÖ beschließen Zusammenarbeit - FPÖ - derStandard.at › Inland |website=Derstandard.at |date= |accessdate=2016-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derwesten.de/politik/afd-und-fpoe-proben-in-duesseldorf-den-schulterschluss-id11563330.html |title=AfD und FPÖ probten in Düsseldorf den Schulterschluss &#124; WAZ.de |language=de|website=Derwesten.de |date=2016-02-14 |accessdate=2016-04-03}}</ref> In April 2016, AfD's vice-president [[Alexander Gauland]] also proposed an alliance with [[Marine Le Pen]]'s [[National Rally (France)|National Rally]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/politik/deutschland/afd-vize-alexander-gauland-erwaegt-offenbar-fraktion-mit-front-national-a-1086442.html |title=AfD-Vize Alexander Gauland erwägt offenbar Fraktion mit Front National - SPIEGEL ONLINE |website=Spiegel.de |date=2016-04-10 |accessdate=2016-04-22}}</ref> Therefore, AfD's MEP [[Marcus Pretzell]] joined the [[Europe of Nations and Freedom]] group on 30 April 2016.

In February 2017, French MEP [[Edouard Ferrand]] met with [[Vox (Spanish political party)|VOX]]'s leaders during a meeting of the Spanish right-wing party.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.voxespana.es/castellon/edouard-ferrand-del-frente-nacional-frances-amigos-de-vox-no-estais-solos-somos-capaces-hoy-por-hoy-de-proponer-un-proyecto-europeo-alternativo-al-actual |title=Edouard Ferrand, del Frente Nacional francés: "Amigos de VOX, no estáis solos. Somos capaces hoy por hoy de proponer un proyecto europeo alternativo al actual" |publisher=VOX Partido Político Castellón |date=2017-02-25 |accessdate=2017-03-17}}</ref> Back in 2016, VOX's president [[Santiago Abascal]] had already met with one of the [[National Rally (France)|National Rally]]'s leaders, [[Louis Aliot]], also one of MENL's MEP in the European Parliament.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elconfidencial.com/espana/2016-11-11/partido-politico-vox-santiago-abascal-reunion-louis-aliot-frente-nacional-marine-le-pen_1288574/ |title=Vox busca la fórmula del éxito de Le Pen con el Frente Nacional. Noticias de España |publisher=Elconfidencial.com |date=2017-01-15 |accessdate=2017-03-17}}</ref>

